282/*******************************************************************************
283 * PGRAPH engine/subdev functions
284 ******************************************************************************/
285
286void
287gm107_gr_init_bios(struct gf100_gr *gr)
288{
289 static const struct {
290 u32 ctrl;
291 u32 data;
292 } regs[] = {
293 { 0x419ed8, 0x419ee0 },
294 { 0x419ad0, 0x419ad4 },
295 { 0x419ae0, 0x419ae4 },
296 { 0x419af0, 0x419af4 },
297 { 0x419af8, 0x419afc },
298 };
299 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
300 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
301 struct nvbios_P0260E infoE;
302 struct nvbios_P0260X infoX;
303 int E = -1, X;
304 u8 ver, hdr;
305
306 while (nvbios_P0260Ep(bios, ++E, &ver, &hdr, &infoE)) {
307 if (X = -1, E < ARRAY_SIZE(regs)) {
308 nvkm_wr32(device, regs[E].ctrl, infoE.data);
309 while (nvbios_P0260Xp(bios, ++X, &ver, &hdr, &infoX))
310 nvkm_wr32(device, regs[E].data, infoX.data);
311 }
312 }
313}
314
315static int
316gm107_gr_init(struct gf100_gr *gr)
317{
318 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
319 const u32 magicgpc918 = DIV_ROUND_UP(0x00800000, gr->tpc_total);
320 u32 data[TPC_MAX / 8] = {};
321 u8 tpcnr[GPC_MAX];
322 int gpc, tpc, ppc, rop;
323 int i;
324
325 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0880), 0x00000000);
326 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0890), 0x00000000);
327 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0894), 0x00000000);
328 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x08b4), nvkm_memory_addr(gr->unk4188b4) >> 8);
329 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x08b8), nvkm_memory_addr(gr->unk4188b8) >> 8);
330
331 gf100_gr_mmio(gr, gr->func->mmio);
332
333 gm107_gr_init_bios(gr);
334
335 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(0, 0x3018), 0x00000001);
336
337 memset(data, 0x00, sizeof(data));
338 memcpy(tpcnr, gr->tpc_nr, sizeof(gr->tpc_nr));
339 for (i = 0, gpc = -1; i < gr->tpc_total; i++) {
340 do {
341 gpc = (gpc + 1) % gr->gpc_nr;
342 } while (!tpcnr[gpc]);
343 tpc = gr->tpc_nr[gpc] - tpcnr[gpc]--;
344
345 data[i / 8] |= tpc << ((i % 8) * 4);
346 }
347
348 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0980), data[0]);
349 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0984), data[1]);
350 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0988), data[2]);
351 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x098c), data[3]);
352
353 for (gpc = 0; gpc < gr->gpc_nr; gpc++) {
354 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0914),
355 gr->magic_not_rop_nr << 8 | gr->tpc_nr[gpc]);
356 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0910), 0x00040000 |
357 gr->tpc_total);
358 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0918), magicgpc918);
359 }
360
361 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x3fd4), magicgpc918);
362 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x08ac), nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100800));
363
364 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400500, 0x00010001);
365
366 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400100, 0xffffffff);
367 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40013c, 0xffffffff);
368 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400124, 0x00000002);
369 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409c24, 0x000e0000);
370
371 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x404000, 0xc0000000);
372 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x404600, 0xc0000000);
373 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x408030, 0xc0000000);
374 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x404490, 0xc0000000);
375 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x406018, 0xc0000000);
376 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x407020, 0x40000000);
377 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405840, 0xc0000000);
378 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405844, 0x00ffffff);
379 nvkm_mask(device, 0x419cc0, 0x00000008, 0x00000008);
380
381 for (gpc = 0; gpc < gr->gpc_nr; gpc++) {
382 for (ppc = 0; ppc < 2 /* gr->ppc_nr[gpc] */; ppc++)
383 nvkm_wr32(device, PPC_UNIT(gpc, ppc, 0x038), 0xc0000000);
384 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0420), 0xc0000000);
385 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0900), 0xc0000000);
386 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x1028), 0xc0000000);
387 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0824), 0xc0000000);
388 for (tpc = 0; tpc < gr->tpc_nr[gpc]; tpc++) {
389 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x508), 0xffffffff);
390 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x50c), 0xffffffff);
391 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x224), 0xc0000000);
392 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x48c), 0xc0000000);
393 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x084), 0xc0000000);
394 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x430), 0xc0000000);
395 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x644), 0x00dffffe);
396 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x64c), 0x00000005);
397 }
398 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x2c90), 0xffffffff);
399 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x2c94), 0xffffffff);
400 }
401
402 for (rop = 0; rop < gr->rop_nr; rop++) {
403 nvkm_wr32(device, ROP_UNIT(rop, 0x144), 0x40000000);
404 nvkm_wr32(device, ROP_UNIT(rop, 0x070), 0x40000000);
405 nvkm_wr32(device, ROP_UNIT(rop, 0x204), 0xffffffff);
406 nvkm_wr32(device, ROP_UNIT(rop, 0x208), 0xffffffff);
407 }
408
409 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0xffffffff);
410 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400138, 0xffffffff);
411 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400118, 0xffffffff);
412 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400130, 0xffffffff);
413 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40011c, 0xffffffff);
414 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400134, 0xffffffff);
415
416 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400054, 0x2c350f63);
417
418 gf100_gr_zbc_init(gr);
419
420 return gf100_gr_init_ctxctl(gr);
421}
